Should get someone from the foundation team to look through these changes.

There is one more dependency we need to take care of: The newget_libhdfs_files script to build the native Hadoop libraries needs cmake, so we need to do the following on all of our machines:

sudo yum -y install cmake

I'll work with Steve to get that done before we can merge the change. This is the reason why the Jenkins test above failed.

I changed the build wiki page to include this dependency.

Hi Steve, 

Could you please help in setting up icu4.4 so that both prefixes work ( with and without Nv44 ) - thanks for your help. This should help in getting the build and packaging step to succeed.
Steps :
1.      cd $TOOLSDIR/icu4.4/linux64/lib
2.      ln -s libicudataNv44.so.44 libicudata.so.44
3.      ln -s  libicuucNv44.so.44 libicuuc.so.44

1. Could you also handle the other comments too (openssl version and build_os.bat) ?
2. Also should we keep the code for SetCertificateDir for later use to provide alternate location for storing certificate.
3. Is UpdateDSN code not needed now ?
4. Could you also look at the Krypton directory for Apache text ?
5. Since currently we don't have a build environment to test this change, could you please do the testing via odbc administrator and odbctest to see that new package works fine - thanks for taking this extra step.

3. It has been deprecated for a long time. 
4. This PR only care about the build tool. We'd better to create a new PR for it if needed.
5. New package works well in my environment . However it's better if anyone else can test it for me since my environment is not a new ,clean OS.
